# Flagify Feature Flags

This project uses the Flagify SDK for feature flag management.

## When writing code that involves feature flags:

1. Import from @flagify/node (server) or @flagify/react (client)
2. Use isEnabled(flagName, context) for boolean flags
3. Use getVariant(flagName, context) for A/B tests
4. Use getValue(flagName, context, fallback) for config values
5. Always include userId in the context object
6. Always handle both enabled and disabled states
7. Flag names are kebab-case: 'feature-name'

## Environments: development, staging, production

To check current flags, run: `npx flagify flags list`
